{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GK9Lcc8Wgewk89iXSMDk6N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me plan the certificate rotation:\n\n1. The TLS certs are mounted directly from the `es-http-tls` secret into the pods at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/`\n2. The ES config references:\n   - `tls.key` - the leaf private key\n   - `tls.crt` - the leaf certificate\n   - `ca.crt` - the CA certificate\n\nFor the rotation, I need to:\n1. Generate a new CA key + self-signed cert (valid 1 year) \n2. Create a new leaf key and CSR signed by that CA, making sure to preserve the same SANs (localhost, *.elasticsearch.svc, *.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local)\n3. Update the `es-http-tls` secret with the new key, certificate, and CA cert\n4. Refresh the `es-http-ca` ConfigMap with the updated CA certificate\n5. Trigger a rolling restart of both StatefulSets so the pods load the new certificates\n\nTo minimize downtime, I'll update the secret first, then perform the rolling restart so pods pick up the new certs as they come back online.\n\nI can use the `openssl-toolbox` pod that's already running in the namespace to generate the certificates. Let me first examine what's currently in the secret to see exactly what fields I'm working with.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1969,"cache_read_input_tokens":37305,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1969},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b217705c-a87c-474b-b084-10a50ec2e055","uuid":"866c709a-0bc6-49da-921e-4083c38a267c","request_id":"req_011CcP4DX5V6riZ2Du1htsQ2"}
